</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(112, 184, 255);">git</span><span> clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/zarik.git
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(251, 173, 96);">cd</span><span> zarik
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(129, 136, 152);"># 2. Run setup</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(112, 184, 255);">chmod</span><span> +x setup.sh
</span></span><span>./setup.sh
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(129, 136, 152);"># 3. Create .env</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(112, 184, 255);">nano</span><span> .env
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(129, 136, 152);"># paste your keys (no quotes)</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(129, 136, 152);"># 4. Test it works</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(251, 173, 96);">source</span><span> venv/bin/activate
</span></span><span>python main.py
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(129, 136, 152);"># Ctrl+C once you see it running</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(129, 136, 152);"># 5. Make it run 24/7</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(112, 184, 255);">sudo</span><span> </span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(112, 184, 255);">cp</span><span> zarik.service /etc/systemd/system/
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(112, 184, 255);">sudo</span><span> systemctl </span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(251, 173, 96);">enable</span><span> zarik
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(112, 184, 255);">sudo</span><span> systemctl start zarik</span></span></code></pre></div></div>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">zarik.service</code> file is a systemd unit — it's how Linux runs things 24/7. <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">Restart=always</code> means if it crashes, it restarts in 5 seconds. <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">enable</code> means it auto-starts on VM reboot. No Docker needed.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Useful commands after setup:</p>
